n%20'liabilities%20of%20ARC%2C'%20including%20'bona%20fide%20creditors%2C%20such%20as%20professional%20advisors%20or%20noteholders%2C%20as%20well%20as%20costs%20imposed%20upon%20ARC%20through%20litigation%2C'%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20that%20Orlando%20emailed%20ARC%20Global%20members%20again%20in%20October%20%26quot%3Bstating%20that%20'%5Bi%5Dnitial%20distributions%20%5Bwere%5D%20in%20progress%2C'%20but%20that%20'further%20distributions'%20were%20only%20'expected%20in%20the%20future.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOrlando's%20email%20again%20alludes%20to%20'attacks'%20on%20ARC%20and%20the%20need%20to%20'defend%20itself%2C'%20without%20providing%20any%20explanation%20for%20how%20such%20'attacks'%20affect%20ARC's%20ability%20to%20tender%20to%20subscribing%20investors%20their%20TMTG%20shares%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsec-sues-ex-ceo-spac-helped-trump-media-for-fraud-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESecurities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20sued%20Orlando%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%2C%20alleging%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bfalsely%20represented%26quot%3B%20that%20his%20blank%20check%20company%2C%20Digital%20World%20Acquisition%20Corp.%2C%20did%20not%20intend%20to%20merge%20with%20any%20specific%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOrlando%20knew%20these%20statements%20were%20false%20because%20he%20had%20personally%20engaged%20in%20numerous%20lengthy%20discussions%20with%20representatives%20of%20Trump%20Media%20%26amp%3B%20Technology%20Group%20Corp%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20SEC%20said%20in%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20of%20investors%20who%20filed%20the%20latest%20lawsuit%20against%20Orlando%20are%20seeking%20to%20recover%20their%20%26quot%3Brightful%20portion%26quot%3B%20of%20the%208.1%20million%20stock%20shares%2C%20%26quot%3Bnullify%20improper%20transactions%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20monetary%20damages.%3C%2F