j%20Misra%20and%20Satish%20Chandra%20Sharma%20had%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20on%20the%20question%20on%20February%201%20after%20hearing%20arguments%20for%20eight%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%201%2C%20grappling%20with%20the%20intractable%20issue%20of%20the%20AMU's%20minority%20status%2C%20the%20top%20court%20said%20the%201981%20amendment%20to%20the%20AMU%20Act%2C%20which%20effectively%20accorded%20it%20a%20minority%20status%2C%20only%20did%20a%20%26quot%3Bhalf-hearted%20job%26quot%3B%20and%20did%20not%20restore%20to%20the%20institution%20the%20position%20it%20had%20prior%20to%201951.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20AMU%20Act%2C%201920%2C%20speaks%20about%20incorporating%20a%20teaching%20and%20residential%20Muslim%20university%20in%20Aligarh%2C%20the%201951%20amendment%20does%20away%20with%20compulsory%20religious%20instructions%20for%20the%20Muslim%20students%20at%20the%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vexed%20question%20has%20repeatedly%20tested%20Parliament's%20legislative%20acumen%20and%20judiciary's%20prowess%20in%20interpreting%20complex%20laws%20involving%20the%20institution%20that%20was%20founded%20in%201875%20as%20Muhammadan%20Anglo-Oriental%20College%20by%20prominent%20Muslim%20community%20members%20led%20by%20Sir%20Syed%20Ahmed%20Khan.%20Years%20later%2C%20in%201920%2C%20it%20transformed%20into%20a%20university%20under%20the%20British%20Raj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20which%20is%20worrying%20us%20is%20that%20the%201981%20amendment%20does%20not%20restore%20the%20position%20as%20it%20stood%20prior%20to%201951.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%201981%20amendment%20does%20a%20half-hearted%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20had%20said%20while%20proceeding%20to%20close%20the%20arguments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20understand%20if%20the%201981%20amendment%20had%20said...%20okay%2C%20we%20are%20going%20back%20to%20the%20original%201920%20statute%2C%20confer%20complete%20minority%20character%20on%20this%20(institution)%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CJI%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20government%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%201981%20amendment%20to%20the%20AMU%20Act%20and%20insisted%20that%20the%20court%20should%20go%20by%20the%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20verdict%20in%20the%20S%20Azeez%20Basha%20versus%20Union%20of%20India%20case%20in%201967.%20The%20Constitution%20bench%20had%20then%20held%20that%20since%20the%20AMU%20was%20a%20central%20university%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20considered%20a%20minority%20institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20said%20it%20needs%20to%20see%20what%20the%201981%20amendment%20did%20and%20whether%20it%20restored%20to%20the%20institution%20the%20status%20it%20enjoyed%20before%201951.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20put%20forward%20the%20view%20favouring%20a%20minority%20status%20for%20the%20institution%2C%20including%20veteran%20lawyer%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20contended%20that%20the%20mere%20fact%20that%20only%2037%20members%20of%20the%20180-member%20governing%20council%20are%20Muslim%20does%20not%20detract%20from%20its%20credentials%20as%20a%20Muslim%20minority%20institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20like%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20contended%20a%20university%20getting%20enormous%20funds%20from%20the%20Centre%20and%20having%20been%20declared%20an%20institution%20of%20national%20importance%20cannot%20claim%20to%20belong%20to%20a%20particular%20religious%20denomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20also%20argued%20that%20once%20the%20Muhammadan%20Anglo-Oriental%20College%20transformed%20itself%20into%20a%20university%20after%20the%201951%20amendment%20to%20the%20AMU%20Act%20and%20began%20receiving%20funds%20from%20the%20Central%20government%2C%20the%20institution%20surrendered%20its%20minority%20character.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lawyer%20disfavouring%20minority%20status%20to%20the%20AMU%20had%20claimed%20that%20it%20received%20over%20Rs%205%2C000%20crore%20from%20the%20Central%20government%20between%202019%20and%202023%2C%20nearly%20double%20what%20the%20University%20of%20Delhi%2C%20a%20central%20university%2C%20got.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20them%20had%20even%20contended%20that%20prominent%20people%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community%20who%20had%20lobbied%20with%20the%20then%20British%20government%20for%20establishing%20the%20institution%20as%20a%20university%20wedded%20to%20the%20cause%20of%20promoting%20education%20among%20the%20Muslims%20did%20not%20consider%20themselves%20as%20a%20religious%20minority%20in%20undivided%20India%20and%20advocated%20a%20two-nation%20theory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sibal%20had%20mounted%20a%20spirited%20counterattack%2C%20asserting%20that%20Article%2030%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20deals%20with%20the%20right%20of%20religious%20and%20linguistic%20minorities%20to%20establish%20and%20administer%20educational%20institutions%20was%20applicable%20to%20the%20AMU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20had%20struck%20down%20the%20provision%20of%20the%201981%20law%20by%20which%20the%20university%20was%20accorded%20minority%20status.%20Appeals%20were%20filed%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20including%20by%20the%20AMU%2C%20against%20the%20high%20court%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20row%20over%20AMU's%20minority%20status%20has%20been%20caught%20in%20a%20legal%20maze%20for%20the%20last%20several%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%2C%20on%20February%2012%2C%202019%2C%20referred%20to%20a%20seven-judge%20bench%20the%20contentious%20issue.%20A%20similar%20reference%20was%20also%20made%20in%201981.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress-led%20UPA%20government%20at%20the%20Centre%20moved%20an%20appeal%20against%20the%202006%20verdict%20of%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20that%20quashed%20the%201981%20amendment%20to%20the%20AMU%20Act.%20The%20university%20also%20filed%20a%20separate%20petition%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NDA%20government%20spearheaded%20by%20the%20BJP%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202016%20that%20it%20would%20withdraw%20the%20appeal%20filed%20by%20the%20UPA%20dispensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20cited%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%201967%20judgement%20in%20the%20Basha%20case%20to%20claim%20that%20AMU%20was%20not%20a%20minority%20institution%20since%20it%20was%20a%20central%20university%20funded%20by%20the%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731003360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-04%2Fs1957ve_aligarh-muslim-university-650_625x300_06_April_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Famu-minority-status-is-aligarh-muslim-university-a-minority-institution-big-supreme-court-verdict-today-6967333%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20scheduled%20to%20pronounce%20its%20verdict%20on%20Friday%20on%20a%20vexed%20legal%20question%20whether%20the%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20(AMU)%20enjoys%20minority%20status%20under%20Article%2030%20of%20the%20Constitution.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Famu-minority-status-is-aligarh-muslim-university-a-minority-institution-big-supreme-court-verdict-today-6967333%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Singham%20Again'%20worldwide%20box%20office%20collection%20day%206%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731003136000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-115061648%2Cimgsize-50902.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fbox-office%2Fsingham-again-worldwide-box-office-collection-day-6-the-ajay-devgn-kareena-kapoor-starrer-inches-close-to-rs-250-crore