peaking%20about%20the%20mood%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20the%20US%20President%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20for%20some%20people%2C%20this%20is%20a%20time%20for%20victory%20and%20celebration%2C%20while%20for%20others%20it%20may%20be%20a%20time%20of%20loss%20and%20despair.%20Campaigns%20are%20a%20contest%20of%20competing%20visions%20The%20country%20chooses%20one%20or%20the%20other.%20And%20we%20all%20must%20accept%20the%20choice%20that%20the%20country%20made.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReaching%20out%20to%20fellow%20Americans%2C%20the%20President%20had%20a%20piece%20of%20advice%20-%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20said%20this%20many%20times%20-%20that%20you%20cannot%20love%20your%20country%20only%20when%20you%20win.%20You%20can't%20love%20your%20neighbour%20only%20when%20you%20agree%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20President%20went%20on%20to%20make%20a%20request%20to%20all%20Americans.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20something%20I%20hope%20you%20all%20can%20do%2C%20no%20matter%20who%20you%20voted%20for...%20to%20see%20each%20other%20not%20as%20adversaries%2C%20but%20as%20fellow%20Americans.%20Bring%20down%20the%20temperature.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20further%20to%20the%20American%20people%2C%20President%20Biden%20had%20words%20of%20advice%20for%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20though%20he%20did%20not%20name%20him%20directly.%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20hope%20that%20we%20can%20later%20lay%20to%20rest%20the%20question%20about%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20American%20electoral%20system.%20It%20is%20honest%2C%20it%20is%20fair%2C%20it%20is%20transparent%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20trusted%20-%20whether%20we%20win%20or%20lose.%20I%20also%20hope%20we%20can%20restore%20the%20respect%20for%20all%20our%20election%20workers%2C%20who%20have%20busted%20their%20necks%20and%20took%20risks%20at%20the%20outset.%20We%20should%20thank%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssuring%20the%20nation%20of%20a%20peaceful%20transition%20of%20power%20at%20the%20White%20House%2C%20President%20Bide