20new%20five-day%20in-office%20mandate%2C%20which%20is%20set%20to%20begin%20in%20January.%20In%20a%20letter%20to%20AWS%20CEO%20Matt%20Garman%2C%20523%20employees%20voiced%20opposition%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Breturn%20to%20office%26quot%3B%20policy%20and%20urged%20management%20to%20maintain%20remote%20work%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAWS%20is%20not%20realizing%20its%20full%20potential%20with%20this%20mandate%2C%20and%20it%20is%20setting%20a%20discouraging%20path%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20shared%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seattletimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Famazon%2Famazon-employees-protest-5-day-a-week-office-return%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Seattle%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20stated.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20flexible%20and%20remote%20work%20does%20have%20its%20challenges%2C%20AWS%20has%20always%20been%20a%20company%20that%20tackles%20problems%20in%20innovative%2C%20forward-thinking%20ways%2C%20rather%20than%20falling%20back%20on%20outdated%20solutions%20that%20worked%20in%20the%20past.%20The%20cloud%20computing%20industry%20might%20not%20exist%20today%20if%20we%20had%20held%20onto%20such%20restrictive%20thinking%20in%20our%20early%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20previously%20announced%20in%20a%20memo%20that%20the%20policy%20would%20begin%20on%20January%202%2C%202025.%20Prior%20to%20this%20change%2C%20Amazon%20required%20employees%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20a%20shift%20that%20sparked%20protests%20as%20well.%20About%2015%20months%20after%20that%20initial%20mandate%2C%20Amazon%20is%20now%20expanding%20the%20requirement%20to%20restore%20pre-pandemic%20work%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20letter%20from%20AWS%20employees%20responds%20to%20Garman's%20comments%20at%20an%20AWS%20town%20hall%2C%20where%20he%20suggested%20employees%20who%20don't%20wish%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20new%20five-day%20rule%20could%20explore%20other%20job%20options.%20Last%20week%2C%20Garman%20reiterated%20this%20stance%20in%20an%20interview%2C%20expressing%20confidence%20in%20the%20policy%20and%20stating%20that%20most%20employees%20he%20spoke%20to%20are%20supportive%20of%20the%20change.%20Garman%20and%20Jassy%20have%20acknowledged%20that%20while%20there%20may%20be%20flexibility%20under%20the%20new%20policy%2C%20such%20as%20managers%20occasionally%20working%20from%20home%20for%20specific%20tasks%2C%20the%20core%20requirement%20remains%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAWS%20employees%20argued%20in%20the%20letter%20that%20Garman's%20comments%20do%20not%20align%20with%20their%20own%20experiences%2C%20claiming%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20silencing%20critical%20perspectives%20and%20harming%20our%20culture%20and%20future.%26quot%3B%20They%20also%20contended%20that%20Amazon's%20decision%20lacked%20data-backed%20analysis%2C%20contradicting%20one%20of%20Amazon's%20key%20principles%2C%20and%20noted%20that%20the%20policy%20might%20hinder%20Amazon's%20goal%20of%20becoming%20%26quot%3BEarth's%20best%20employer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mandate%20is%20expected%20to%20particularly%20affect%20employees%20who%20depend%20on%20remote%20work%20flexibility%2C%20such%20as%20those%20with%20disabilities%2C%20caregiving%20duties%2C%20or%20visa%20restrictions.%20The%20employees%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20mandate%20may%20drive%20senior%20staff%20members%20who%20often%20have%20the%20credentials%20and%20financial%20flexibility%20to%20seek%20other%20roles%20away%20from%20Amazon%2C%20potentially%20impacting%20the%20collaborative%20culture%20the%20company%20aims%20to%20foster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20policy%20will%20make%20Amazon%20one%20of%20the%20few%20major%20tech%20companies%20in%20Seattle%20with%20such%20a%20stringent%20in-office%20requirement.%20Starbucks%20recently%20implemented%20a%20similar%20approach%2C%20requiring%20corporate%20employees%20to%20work%20from%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%20starting%20in%20January%2C%20with%20non-compliance%20leading%20to%20potential%20job%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20letter%2C%20AWS%20employees%20reiterated%20their%20desire%20for%20Amazon%20to%20reconsider%20its%20stance%2C%20emphasizing%2C%20%26quot%3BRemote%20and%20flexible%20work%20represents%20an%20opportunity%20for%20Amazon%20to%20lead%2C%20not%20a%20threat.%20We%20want%20to%20work%20for%20leaders%20who%20see%20this%20moment%20as%20a%20chance%20to%20reinvent%20how%20we%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Amazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20said%20at%20an%20all-hands%20meeting%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20the%20plan%20to%20require%20employees%20to%20be%20in-office%20five%20days%20per%20week%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20force%20attrition%20or%20satisfy%20city%20leaders%2C%20as%20many%20employees%20have%20suggested%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20number%20of%20people%20I've%20seen%20theorized%20that%20the%20reason%20we%20were%20doing%20this%20is%2C%20it's%20a%20backdoor%20layoff%2C%20or%20we%20made%20some%20sort%20of%20deal%20with%20city%20or%20cities%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jassy%2C%20according%20to%20a%20transcript%20of%20the%20meeting%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20tell%20you%20both%20of%20those%20are%20not%20true.%20You%20know%2C%20this%20was%20not%20a%20cost%20play%20for%20us.%20This%20is%20very%20much%20about%20our%20culture%20and%20strengthening%20our%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730991240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fjhsuuj3o_amazon-_625x300_07_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgo-work-for-another-company-amazon-group-firm-ceo-to-employees-protesting-end-of-wfh-6966800%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22523%20Amazon%20employees%20protested%20the%20%26quot%3Breturn%20to%20office%26quot%3B%20policy%20and%20urged%20management%20to%20maintain%20remote%20work%20flexibility.%22%2C%22au