t%3B%20Seniors%20Free%20Hand%3A%20WC%20Winner%20Names%20'Ideal'%20India%20Coach%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%201983%20World%20Cup%20winner%20and%20ex-chairman%20of%20selectors%2C%20Sandeep%20Patil%20feels%20John%20Wright's%20approach%20of%20giving%20a%20free-hand%20to%20players%20led%20to%20his%20successful%20coaching%20stint%20with%20India%2C%20something%20his%20more%20authoritarian%20successors%20Greg%20Chappell%20and%20Anil%20Kumble%20failed%20to%20emulate.%20In%20his%20autobiography%20--%20Beyond%20Boundaries%20--%20launched%20here%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Patil%20gave%20deep%20insights%20about%20the%20reason%20behind%20Wright's%20success%20as%20India%20coach%20vis%20a%20vis%20Chappell%20and%20Kumble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%202000%2C%20India%20have%20had%20an%20array%20of%20international%20coaches%20and%20support%20staff.%20This%20has%20paid%20rich%20dividends%2C%20because%20India's%20overseas%20record%20has%20improved%20steadily.%20It%20all%20started%20with%20John%20Wright%20becoming%20India's%20first%20foreign%20coach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20John%20was%20the%20ideal%20coach%20for%20India.%20He%20was%20soft%20spoken%2C%20polite%2C%20well-mannered%2C%20always%20kept%20to%20himself%2C%20and%20was%20happy%20to%20be%20in%20Sourav%20Ganguly's%20shadow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20addition%20to%20all%20that%2C%20he%20kept%20a%20distance%20from%20the%20Press.%20He%20managed%20that%20so%20well%2C%20that%20he%20was%20hardly%20in%20the%20news%20%E2%80%94%20unlike%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20Greg%20Chappell%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Patil%20wrote%20in%20his%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20Chappell%2C%20he%20was%20in%20the%20news%20every%20day.%20It%20is%20very%20important%20for%20a%20coach%20to%20first%20understand%20the%20policy%20of%20that%20particular%20board%2C%20the%20thinking%20of%20the%20board%20members%2C%20and%20the%20President.%20He%20should%20have%20a%20good%20rapport%20with%20the%20President%20and%20the%20Secretary%2C%20and%20of%20course%20the%20captain%20and%20the%20team.%20John%20did%20that%20wonderfully.%26quot%3B%20Patil%20observed%20that%20every%20player%20was%20equal%20and%20the%20team%20came%20first%20for%20Wright.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...during%20his%20tenure%2C%20there%20was%20no%20'seniors'%20and%20juniors'%20business.%20It%20was%20one%20team.%20He%20believed%20all%20seniors%20were%20leaders%20in%20some%20way%2C%20He%20gave%20them%20respect%2C%20and%20a%20free%20hand%2C%20which%20l%20feel%20Anil%20Kumble%20didn't%20do.%20Greg%20Chappell%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20India%20coach%20felt%20that%20Chappell's%20aggressive%20approach%20did%20not%20suit%20the%20Indian%20dressing%20room%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGreg%20is%20a%20very%20strong%20personality%3B%20very%20aggressive.%20The%20moment%20Jagmohan%20Dalmiya%20said%20you%20have%20a%20free%20hand%2C%20he%20thought%20that%20he%20can%20change%20everything%20overnight.%20John%20waited%2C%20and%20learnt%20the%20system.%20Greg%20wanted%20to%20change%20the%20entire%20system%2C%20the%20entire%20thinking%2C%20and%20the%20selection%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Patil%20elaborated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20introduced%20flexibility%20in%20the%20Indian%20team%2C%20and%20he%20spoiled%20things%20for%20Rahul%20Dravid%2C%20who%20took%20over%20from%20Ganguly%20as%20captain.%20Irfan%20(Pathan)%20was%20asked%20to%20move%20up%20the%20order.%20Seniors%20don't%20like%20to%20change%20numbers%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20Sachin%20Tendulkar%2C%20Dravid%2C%20or%20Virender%20Sehwag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20other%20issue%20in%20the%20Greg%20Chappell%20saga%20was%20the%20presence%20of%20Ian%20Fraser%20as%20Assistant%20Coach.%20Most%20players%20didn't%20like%20his%20presence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatil%20said%20Chappell%20was%20in%20a%20hurry%20to%20introduce%20the%20Australian%20culture%20in%20the%20Indian%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGreg%20wanted%20to%20introduce%20the%20Australian%20culture%2C%20the%20Australian%20way%20of%20playing%20cricket%2C%20and%20the%20Australian%20way%20of%20thinking.%20He%20could've%20done%20it%2C%20but%20he%20didn't%20bide%20his%20time.%20That's%20where%20I%20think%20the%20rift%20started%2C%20and%20he%20was%20against%20a%20few%20seniors%20who%20were%20not%20toeing%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSourav%20is%20not%20a%20guy%20who%20will%20get%20up%20and%20start%20running%20and%20doing%20stretches.%20You%20need%20to%20give%20him%20time.%20I%20think%20Greg%20rubbed%20seniors%20the%20wrong%20way%2C%20though%20a%20few%20seniors%20didn't%20speak%20openly%20about%20him%20-%20some%20like%20Kumble%20still%20haven't.%20It's%20the%20same%20with%20Dravid.%20Ironically%2C%20Ganguly%20got%20him%20in%2C%20but%20was%20instrumental%20in%20his%20exit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatil%20felt%20Gary%20Kirsten%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20most%20successful%20Indian%20coach%20because%20of%20his%20closeness%20with%20the%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGary%20Kirsten%20was%20very%20successful%20-%20you%20could%20say%20most%20successful%2C%20because%20his%20squad%20won%20the%202011%20World%20Cup.%20Gary%2C%20again%2C%20was%20well-respected%20and%20soft-spoken.%20He%20had%20played%20against%20the%20same%20players%20and%20got%20runs.%20This%20counts%2C%20in%20a%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20played%20in%20India%2C%20he%20knew%20what%20to%20expect.%20He%20also%20stayed%20away%20from%20the%20Press%2C%20and%20gave%20all%20his%2024%20hours%20to%20the%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730981400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2F6uq51up4_anil-kumble_625x300_16_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fwright-was-ideal-india-coach-he-gave-players-free-hand-unlike-chappell-kumble-sandeep-patil-6962843%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anil%20Kumble's%20exit