%20%3Cem%3Erezala%20%3C%2Fem%3Efrom%20peacock%20meat%20until%20hunting%20peacocks%20was%20banned.%20As%20for%20%3Cem%3Efilfora%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F349748%2Flaal-maas-history-recipe-best-places-to-eat-in-rajasthan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehunting%20traditions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Bhopal.%20Upon%20the%20killing%20of%20an%20animal%20%E2%80%93%20usually%20nilgai%2C%20deer%20or%20gazelle%20%E2%80%93%20its%20meat%20was%20coarsely%20chopped%20or%20sliced%20into%20slivers%20while%20still%20warm%2C%20and%20immediately%20fried%20with%20some%20basic%20ingredients%20on%20a%20campfire.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20made%20for%20a%20rustic%20meal%20for%20the%20hunters.%20The%20modern%20version%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Efilfora%20%3C%2Fem%3Eincludes%20hand-chopped%20mincemeat%20cooked%20with%20ginger%E2%80%93garlic%20paste%2C%20turmeric%2C%20chillies%2C%20onions%2C%20yoghurt%20and%20coriander.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20book%20takes%20its%20course%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20taken%20on%20a%20winding%20journey%20across%20the%20subcontinent.%20From%20%3Cem%3Eqiwami%20seviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(whose%20recipe%20Karachi-based%20writer%20Muneeza%20Shamsie%20chanced%20upon%20after%20her%20mother%E2%80%99s%20passing)%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F266943%2Fwinter-food-map-traditional-indian-recipes-gajar-ka-halwa-nolen-gur-syku-daulat-ki-chaat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewinter%20staple%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Esarson%20ka%20saag%3C%2Fem%3E%20(shared%20by%20Moneeza%20Hashmi%2C%20daughter%20of%20the%20legendary%20poet%20Faiz%20Ahmed%20Faiz)%20to%20historian%20Rana%20Safvi%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Elahsan%20mirch%20ki%20chutney%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20digital%20archivist%20Farah%20Yameen%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Ekaleji%20fry%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eamidst%20others%20%E2%80%94%20each%20chapter%20conjur